  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb2, \u0bb9\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd, \u0bae\u0ba9\u0bc1\u0bb7, \u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bbf\u0b95 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bc8\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bc1 \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0b95\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Bandula, Harin, Manusha and Dhammi resigned from the ministry posts",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Bandula Gunawardena, Hareen Fernando, Manusha Nanayakkara and Thammika Perera have resigned from the cabinet positions headed by President Gotabaya Rajapaksa. They resigned following the people's protest that took place the day before yesterday demanding the resignation of the President and the Prime Minister.",
        "Bandula Gunawardena, who served as the Minister of Transport, Highways and Media Department, resigned the day before yesterday. He has also announced that he has decided to leave the Sri Lanka Podujana Peramuna Party and work independently in the Parliament.",
        "Harin Fernando, who served as the Minister of Tourism and Land Affairs in the government led by Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe, and Manusha Nanayakkara, who served as the Minister of Foreign Employment, have resigned from their ministerial positions the day before yesterday.",
        "Hareen Fernando and Manusha Nanayakkara have mentioned that they have decided to resign from the ministerial posts to form an interim government by uniting all the political parties.",
        "Mahinda Amaraweera has mentioned that he is stepping down from the posts of the Ministry of Agriculture and Forestry after the successful distribution of 40,000 metric tons of urea fertilizer to the farmers under the Indian Loan Assistance Scheme.",
        "Investment Promotion Minister Tammika Perera has informed the President's Secretary in writing yesterday that she is resigning from her posts."
      ],
